# Coding Conventions

## Clean Code
- Write self-documenting code with meaningful variable and function names.
- Keep functions small and focused on a single responsibility (Single Responsibility Principle).
- Use early returns to reduce nesting and improve readability.
- Prefer immutability and pure functions where possible.

## Error Handling
- Fail fast and throw exceptions for unexpected conditions.
- Handle expected errors gracefully and return meaningful error responses.
- Always log errors with sufficient context for debugging.
